The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                GRP assistant sub-inspector Sanjib Chakrabarty, GRP constable Debasish Mukherjee and Pankaj Ghosh were arrested on Monday for allegedly posing as CID officers and robbing Rs 6 lakh from a man on Chittaranjan Avenue on August 11. The trio took the money away claiming the notes were fake.     Monoranjan Roy, the owner of edible oil company Pincon, was arrested at his Jadavpur home on Sunday night for allegedly cheating a nationalised bank of   s 5.5 crore.     Bumba Mukherjee was arrested in Alipore Jail Quarters on Monday in connection with the alleged assault on former footballer and coach Subrata Bhattacharya at the Mohun Bagan ground.    Mithu Jadav, out on bail after being arrested for allegedly raping a minor, was forced by people to offer flowers at her feet on the Howrah court premises on Monday. Additional public prosecutor Nandalal Chatterjee resigned after being accused by NGO Ganatantrik Nagarik Samity of trying to protect Jadav.    Four women were arrested in a house at Tallah on Monday for being allegedly associated with a sleaze racket. Residents said Rima Sen, 45, had been running the racket for several months. She was arrested along with three women in mid-20s.     One person died and four were injured when two trucks collided on Jessore Road on Sunday.    Power cuts at Nimtala burning ghat disrupted cremations for two hours on Monday.    The high court on Monday gave Children Welfare Committee the right to decide where an 11-year-old boy who used to work as a domestic help would stay and study. Neighbours helped the boy, who used to be tortured by his mistress, to flee.                                                                                                                                                              
